        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:04PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 504 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Iraan Municipal Airport, or 19 miles north of
Sheffield, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Crockett County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
